description: From Middle English starkenen (“to grow strong”), equivalent to stark +‎ -en.

adjectives.description: starken (comparative more starken, superlative most starken)

verbs.description: starken (third-person singular simple present starkens, present participle starkening, simple past and past participle starkened)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To make unbending or inflexible; stiffen; make obstinate.
